A weather alert has been issued for the Lower Mainland with up to 50 mm expected to fall overnight Thursday to Friday.

In anticipation of this storm, Mainroad crews said they will be patrolling for flooding problems on all highways.

B.C. Hydro warned in a social media post on Thursday that people living in the path of the storm should be ‚Äúpreparing for possible damage‚Äù and are warning of possible power outages.

The utility company said people should make a list of local emergency contact numbers, get surge protectors to protect sensitive electronics and prepare an emergency kit containing:

‚Ä¢ flashlights;

‚Ä¢ extra batteries;

‚Ä¢ first-aid kit;

‚Ä¢ bottled water;

‚Ä¢ supplies for people with special needs;

‚Ä¢ copy of your preparedness plan;

‚Ä¢ battery or crank-operated clock and radio;

‚Ä¢ corded telephone;

‚Ä¢ non-perishable, ready-to-eat foods;

‚Ä¢ warm clothing and blankets.

